latestPosts.caption:
Why does no one talk about this? Gentle cleansers don’t lather like face washes you’ve grown up using—because they’re not meant to strip your skin dry.

#ad If you have dry and sensitive skin, start by switching your cleanser. You don’t need foam, you need hydration. I use the @cerave.india Hydrating Cleanser (yes, the one that feels like lotion) both AM & PM. It’s loaded with ceramides to support your skin barrier and hyaluronic acid to pull in moisture—so your skin feels soft after cleansing, not tight and flaky.

Quick dry skin tips:
* Avoid hot water—use lukewarm water to cleanse
* Always pat dry, don’t rub your face with a towel
* Apply moisturizer immediately on damp skin
* Limit exfoliation to 2x/week, max

Your cleanser is step one in fixing dryness. Choose one that works with your skin, not against it.

#CeraVeCleansers #CleanseBhiMoisturiseBhi #CeraVe #CleanserThatGivesNotJustTakes @cerave.india

Now before you fight me—this is not hate towards any brand.
I genuinely want every brand to improve and win. I’ve used each sunscreen at-least 5 times, checked the ingredient lists from their official websites or retailers, and pasted them into ChatGPT to check for comedogenic ingredients + fragrance. So the rest of the ratings are based on my experience and opinions.

Which one gets your 10/10?

Sun protection- 3
Fragrance- 1

Eye stinging- 1
